column5: Caracas, Venezuela; New York, New York
column15: Lexi Parra is a Venezuelan-American photographer and community educator based between Caracas and New York. Her work focuses on youth culture, the personal effects of inequality and violence, and themes of resilience. Photos provided by the artist from her personal archive and ongoing work on ballroom and queer culture in Venezuela. All rights reserved by Lexi Parra. Prints and image licensing are available upon request. For more information, please visit her online portfolio site here.

column15: Rebeca Huntt identifies as an Afro-Latina filmmaker who was born and raised in New York City. In Beba , her pulsating opera prima, Huntt reflects on her childhood and adolescence in New York City as the daughter of a Dominican father and a Venezuelan mother. The above photo was taken by Waleska Solórzano during a screening of Huntt's film at The Aster in Los Angeles. For more information on her film, please visit Beba's official site here.
